name: creditCardSystem
description: Project of a microservice for credit card payments

name: warehouse-management-system
description: This Warehouse Management System utilizes a microservices architecture with Go and Kafka, using Postgres and redis, orchestrated via Docker and Kubernetes, to enhance efficiency and scalability in warehouse operations.

name: library-management-system
description: A Library Management System built using Spring Boot and microservices architecture.

name: message-bridge
description: A message routing system through microservices architecture.

name: Ecommerce-MicroServices
description: Product Management System A Java-based micro-services application for streamlined product management, featuring controllers for product creation, updates, categorization, and inventory tracking. Built with Maven for scalability and easy maintenance.

name: Architecure-of-microservices-with-Java
description: This repository covers the architecture of microservices using Java. It includes guidelines and examples for designing scalable, maintainable applications by breaking down large systems into smaller, independent services. Key concepts such as service communication, database management, and deployment strategies are also explored

name: probable-pancake
description: Small pet project testing a system of microservices running Kafka services over Kubernetes

name: Devotel.codechallenge
description: A simple NestJS microservice for blog posts management system with image uploading service. It handles image storage, metadata saving, and serves images through an API. The project includes basic validation, authentication, and role-based access controls.

name: InstaShareBackend
description: InstaShare is a distributed application designed for efficient and secure file sharing and management. It leverages a microservices architecture, asynchronous communication with RabbitMQ, advanced file compression using IronZip, and a distributed file system based on Docker containers.

name: Lily
description: This project focuses on monitoring pregnant women’s health, including glucose levels, calories, and blood sugar. It collects patient data from monitoring devices and serves both doctors and patients. The system is built using a microservices architecture with Node.js and MongoDB Enterprise (encrypted MongoDB) for secure data storage.
